params._initialAuctionPrice: - input the amount in 18 decimals. Since the buy amount is measured in 18 decimals, the initialAuctionprice is the price for the smallest unit of the token
params._tokenAddress: - the address that is being auctioned.
params._totalAuctionAmount: - input the amount but in 18 decimals: so 1 token would be 1000000000000000000. _totalAuctionAmount, _initialAuctionPrice, _timeToEmitAll, _totalAuctionAmount are NOT multiplied with 1e18 This is because we don't want to confuse the user when they call the view functions View functions will return int256s with full token decimals The decimals necessary for SD59x18 calculation will be reserved for internal use

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.numTokens: - please enter amount with full 18 decimals behind (so 1 token would be 1000000000000000000)

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

purchasePrice(uint256).notice: calculate purchase price using exponential continuous GDA formula

purchaseTokens(uint256,address).notice: purchase a specific number of tokens from the GDA
